  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">For GGF funds will be used to implement a sustainable agriculture and hygiene project in the Otuke District of Uganda. The project will fund plow and oxen sets to be distributed to 20 groups of 5 women each (to affect over 800 individuals in sum) which is estimated to increase each family&apos;s agricultural income by 600%. BeadforLife will provide training and support for farmers to increase their organic agriculture productivity and bring their products to market. Finally, this support will allow Bead4Life to distribute sanitary water taps (for people to wash their hands) and educate the households on sanitary hygienic practives. The group estimates it will be able to reach over 5,700 people through this hygiene directive</narrative>
